**Col 3:12-14**
  ~~~ CONTEXT: Col 3:5-11~~~~
  5 Put to death, therefore, whatever belongs to your earthly nature:
    - sexual immorality, 
    - impurity, 
    - lust, 
    - evil desires 
    - and greed, which is idolatry. 
  6 Because of these, the wrath of God is coming.
  7 You used to walk in these ways, in the life you once lived. 
  8 But now you must also rid yourselves of all such things as these: 
    - anger, 
    - rage, 
    - malice, 
    - slander, 
    - and filthy language from your lips. 
  9 Do not lie to each other, 
    - since you have taken off your old self with its practices 
    - 10 and have put on the new self, 
      * which is being renewed in knowledge in the image of its Creator. 
  11 Here there is no 
    - Gentile or Jew, 
    - circumcised or uncircumcised, 
    - barbarian, 
    - Scythian, 
    - slave or free, 
    * but Christ is all, and is in all.
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  12 Therefore, as God’s
    - chosen people,
    - holy
    - and dearly loved,
  clothe yourselves with 
    * compassion, 
    * kindness, 
    * humility, 
    * gentleness
    * and patience.
  13 Bear with each other 
  - and forgive one another if any of you has a grievance against someone.
    * Forgive as the Lord forgave you.
  14 And over all these virtues
    * put on love, which binds them all together in perfect unity.

Clothing:
	Gal 3:26-27
  ~~~CONTEXT~~~
  Faith over Works of the Law, under a curse if maintaining Law but Christ liberates (v1-14)
  Promise (blessing of Abraham and his seed [Christ]) came before the Law (v15-18)
  Law for control of sin so promise given thru faith in Jesus, might be given to those who believe (v19-22)
  We were under Law, it was our guardian, UNTIL Christ came so we may be justified by faith and no longer be under a guardian (v23-25)
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  26 So in Christ Jesus
    - you are all children of God
      ** through faith, **
  27 for all of you
    - who were baptized into Christ
    * have clothed yourselves with Christ.

	Rev 7:13-14
    13 Then one of the elders asked me,
    “These in white robes—who are they,
    and where did they come from?”
    14 I answered, “Sir, you know.”
    And he said, “These are they who have come out of the great tribulation;
      - they have washed their robes
      - and made them white
        ** in the blood of the Lamb. **
  
	Ro 13:[13]-14
  ~~CONTEXT~~~
  Submitting to Authorities, do not fear and do good (v1-7)
  Love fulfills the Law (v8-10)
  Day is near...WAKE UP, salvation is nearer every day, putting aside darkness...(v11-13)
    "So let us put aside the deeds of darkness 
    and put on the armor of light." (v12)
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~
    14 Rather, clothe yourselves with
      * the Lord Jesus Christ,
      - and do not think about how to gratify the desires of the flesh.
	
  1Pe 3:3-4\
    3 Your beauty should not come from outward adornment,
        such as elaborate hairstyles
        and the wearing of gold jewelry
        or fine clothes.
    4 Rather, it should be that of your inner self,
      - the unfading beauty of 
        * a gentle
        * and quiet spirit,
    which is of great worth in God’s sight.

  Mt 6:25
    25 “Therefore I tell you, do not worry about your life, what you will eat or drink; 
    or about your body, what you will wear. 
    Is not life more than food, 
    and the body more than clothes?
	
