	  Jas 2:1-4
      1 My brothers and sisters,
      believers in our glorious Lord Jesus Christ must not show favoritism. 
      2 Suppose a man comes into your meeting wearing a gold ring and fine clothes, 
      and a poor man in filthy old clothes also comes in.
      3 If you show special attention to the man wearing fine clothes and say, 
      “Here’s a good seat for you,” 
      but say to the poor man,
      “You stand there” or “Sit on the floor by my feet,”
      4 have you not discriminated among yourselves and become judges with evil thoughts?

    Rev 7:9-10
      9 After this I looked, and there before me was a great multitude that no one could count,
      from every nation, tribe, people and language, standing before the throne and before the Lamb. 
        - They were wearing white robes
        - and were holding palm branches in their hands.
      10 And they cried out in a loud voice:
        “Salvation belongs to our God,
        who sits on the throne,
        and to the Lamb.”

Gen 3:21
  21 The Lord God made garments of skin for Adam and his wife and clothed them.


Clothes
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
First rid or take off:
- sexual immorality
- impurity
- lust
- evil desires
- greed (idolatry)

- anger
- rage
- malice
- slander
- filthy language from your lips
- do not lie to each other
- your old self with its practices

- the deeds of darkness
- gratifying the desires of the flesh

- outward adornment (elaborate hairstyles, gold jewlry, fine clothes)

- worries
	- about your life, what you will eat or drink
	- about your body, what you will wear
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Then put on:
- your new self which is being renewed in knowledge in the image of its Creator.
	- image where there is no Genitle or Jew, Circumcised or uncircumcised, barbarian, scythian, slave or free
	  but CHRIST IS ALL AND IS IN ALL
	- YOU are God's CHOSEN people, HOLY, and DEARLY LOVED.
- Compassion
- Kindness
- Humility
- Gentleness
- and Patience

- Bear with each other
- Forgive one another
* just as Lord forgave you
***above all put on LOVE***
	- Love binds these all together in perfect unity

- Christ (clothed in Him when baptized)
- Washed robes, making them white, in the blood of the Lamb

- the armor of light

- inner self
	- unfading beauty of a GENTLE and QUIET spirit

- Faith and Trust in God to clothe you



















































